QUENNE International Research Consortium (QIRC)

A Global Collaboration for Regulated Autonomous Intelligence

Proposal Version: 1.0
Year: 2026
Lead Institution: QUENNE Research Institute (Japan)
Founder & Doctrine Steward: Nicolas E. Santiago

â¸»

1. Executive Overview

The QUENNE International Research Consortium (QIRC) is proposed as a neutral, multi-national research alliance dedicated to the scientific development, validation, and governance of regulated autonomous intelligence.

QIRC is established to address a growing global challenge:

Advanced intelligence systems are increasing in autonomy faster than our ability to ensure their stability, safety, and long-term societal alignment.

The consortium unites academic institutions, public research agencies, and non-commercial partners under a shared architectural doctrine, ensuring that autonomy evolves responsibly and coherently across borders.

â¸»

